               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>This manuscript contains an incomplete copy of the <title xml:lang="sa">Nyāyarakṣāmaṇi</title> of <persName xml:lang="sa">Appaya Dīkṣita</persName>, a commentary on the <title xml:lang="sa">Brahmasūtra</title>. It breaks off in the middle of the commentary on <term xml:lang="sa">sūtra 1.1.13</term>, <q xml:lang="sa">ānandamayo 'bhyāsāt</q> (<locus facs="45">21v</locus>, line 5).</p>
<p>In Cabaton's catalogue entry, Sanscrit 1108 and 1109 have been mixed up.</p></summary>
                  
               <msItem defective="true"><title xml:lang="sa">Nyāyarakṣāmaṇi</title><author xml:lang="sa">Appaya Dīkṣita</author><textLang mainLang="san"/><incipit xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="1r" unit="folio" facs="4"/>
<lb n="1"/>ut_dhāṭya yogakalayā hṛdayābjakośaṃ | dhanyaiś cirād api yathāruci gṛhyamāṇaḥ | yaḥ prasphuraty avirataṃ paripurṇṇarūpaś śreyas same diśatu śāśvatikaṃ mukundaḥ |</incipit><explicit xml:lang="sa"><milestone n="23v" unit="folio" facs="49"/>
<lb n="6"/><gap reason="ellipsis"/>tadā brahmaṇaḥ pucśa<lb n="7"/>tvakalpanasya <unclear>ślo</unclear>kād api prathamaśrutatvena śiraḥpakṣamadhyapucśāvayavayuktasyānandamayasya prādhānyāvagamāt – brahma<pb n="24r" facs="50"/><unclear>padā</unclear>bhyāsavān nigamana<unclear>ślo</unclear>ko py ānandamayaviṣaya iti kalpyatāṃ | tasmād ānandamaya eva prādhānyena pratipādya iti pūrvapa<lb n="2"/>kṣaḥ evaṃ prāpte siddhānta ucyate | ānandamayo bhyāsād iti – ānandamayavākye śrūtaṃ pucśa</explicit></msItem></msContents>
